Instructions to install matplotlib for Bash for Windows
  1. Make sure Anaconda is installed
  2. type:
          conda install matplotlib
  3. type:
          apt-get update
          apt install libgl1-mesa-glx
  4. google "xming" and download from sourcefourge.net
  5. type: 
         sudo apt-get install x11-apps
  6. type:
         export DISPLAY=localhost:0.0 (you can also add to your ~/.bashrc to make it permanent
         
  7.type:
          sudo apt-get install gnome-calculator (to get GTK)
  8.edit matplotlibrc and change backend :TKAgg
      You might find matplotlibrc in /home/<yourhomedirectory>/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/matplotlib/mpl-data/matplotlibrc
  
